  description: "concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor.shutdown and map qualname, doc, and code checks — shutdown.__qualname__.__eq__('ThreadPoolExecutor.shutdown')==True (len=27: 'ThreadPoolExecutor'=18+'.'=1+'shutdown'=8=27; tied with __init__ for longest qualname in this spec); shutdown.__module__.__eq__('concurrent.futures.thread')==True (len=25: same thread module as __init__ and submit); shutdown.__doc__.__len__()==491 (a multi-paragraph doc describing wait and cancel_futures behaviour — the longest __doc__ of the ThreadPoolExecutor-specific methods in this spec); shutdown.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__(2)==True ('self','wait'); shutdown.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==5 ('self','wait','cancel_futures','work_item','t' — 2 params + 3 locals); map.__qualname__.__eq__('Executor.map')==True (len=12: the shortest qualname in this spec because map is defined on the Executor base class, not ThreadPoolExecutor directly; 'Executor'=8+'.'=1+'map'=3=12); map.__module__.__eq__('concurrent.futures._base')==True (len=24: the base module, not thread); map.__doc__.__len__()==1063 (the longest __doc__ in this spec: multi-paragraph with detailed parameter descriptions); map.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__(2)==True ('self','fn'); map.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==8 ('self','fn','timeout','chunksize','buffersize','iterables','args','result_iterator' — 2 params + 6 locals); verified with Python 3.14.3"
